## Fix: Domain access roster now shares the Teams matrix source

**Context**: Locally the new "Domain access" roster listed several principals
that the Registry → Teams page did not show. Root cause: the Teams matrix
(`build_teams_matrix_result`) renders one row per **Databricks App principal**
(`list_app_principals`) and overlays the per-domain role onto those rows, so a
`.domain_permissions.json` entry whose principal is no longer in the App ACL
(an orphan assignment, common in local/test data) is invisible there. The first
cut of `review_team` instead listed the **raw** `.domain_permissions.json`
entries, so those orphans surfaced — making the two views disagree.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/objects/registry/ReviewService.py` — `review_team` now builds the
   roster from the **same source as the Teams matrix**: it fetches the App
   principals (`permission_service.list_app_principals`) and the per-domain
   entries (`list_domain_entries`), then emits a member only when an App
   principal (user by email, group by name) has an assignable role on the
   domain. This is exactly the "filled cells" of the domain's column in the
   Teams matrix, so the Validation roster and the Teams page are now
   guaranteed consistent. Orphan permission entries are no longer shown.
2. `tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py` — reworked the `review_team`
   tests to mock both the App ACL and the per-domain entries; added
   `test_review_team_excludes_entries_without_app_principal` (the exact
   regression) and `test_review_team_includes_groups`.

**Modified files**:
- `src/back/objects/registry/ReviewService.py`
- `tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py`

**Test result**: `pytest tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py
tests/units/api/test_review_endpoints.py` → **61 passed**. No new lint errors.
